                              JERRY GREENBERG
                                      
                     Chairman of the Board of Directors
                                      
   Mr. Greenberg is a co-founder and major shareholder of the Company.
   From 1982 to 1989 he was the sole shareholder and President of Leader
   Communications Inc. (Leader), a Chicago based cellular phone and
   two-way radio company. In 1989, Mr. Greenberg sold Leader
   Communications to Fleet Call, Inc., which subsequently changed its
   name to NextTel. Prior to owning and operating Leader, Mr. Greenberg
   was the President of Hampden Green Management Corporation, a private
   real estate management and development company.
   
